The newly confirmed cases include the first one outside the capital Addis Ababa a 61-year-old man in Adama, 100 kilometres  east of the capital. Other confirmed cases are a 71-year-old Mauritian and two Ethiopian women in their 20s.

Meanwhile on Friday morning, the South African National Health Department released a statement confirming the deaths of two people. 

One at a private hospital and the other at a public health facility.
